p armament= |Ship armour= |Ship armor= |Ship notes= }} |}
The '''SS ''Cheduba''''' was the third ship built at [[A and J Inglis]], Pointhouse, Glasgow.<ref>Paul Strathdee and Stuart Cameron:[http://www.clydesite.co.uk/clydebuilt/viewship.asp?id=1653 Cheduba (1863) of A and J Inglis]</ref> She was probably built in collaboration with Archibald Denny Dumbarton and launched on Saturday, 18 April 1863.<ref>George Robinson and Stuart Cameron: [http://www.clydesite.co.uk/clydebuilt/viewship.asp?id=12086 Launched 1863: SS Cheduba of Archibald Denny Dumbarton.]</ref>
''Cheduba'' was owned by British India Steam Navigation Company Glasgow. She sank with the loss of all hands in the [[Bay of Bengal]] on 15 May 1869 while on passage from [[Calcutta]] to [[Rangoon]].
